commit.message: Fixed AboutFragment display problem in a disgusting display of hacky code

Added ability to tap on chat heading to expand/collapse

Also included Toast if chat messages cannot be fetched.

Fixed message time display and timezone

Now each message displays the time it was sent at (not the date, in
keeping with the website's way of doing things). Also, as the website
sends out message times w.r.t. GMT, the app converts the received time
to the user's current timezone.

Now sends and receives messages

Automatically receives 10 newest messages on start-up. Listens for new
message events on socket and updates chat view accordingly. Can send
messages from app as well.

TODO: Fix timestamp display, implement loading earlier messages (tried
some form of auto-loading on scroll up, but that's being kind of wonky
right now).
Added socket disconnect code (and switched to local server)
Merged MainActivity due to outdated local repo
Finalized chat UI; added dummy messages for showcasing
General commit; don't remember what changes I made here lol if any
